st?\n\n- Kiera Woodhull, Chaos of the Mind\n|\nYou are the trembling of time, that passesbetween vertical light and darkened sky,\n\n- Pablo Neruda, 100 Love Sonnets\n|\nA child is conceived in a womb of a woman, miraculously, in sacred moment of conception.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nTo stand up straight and tread the turning mill,To lie flat and know nothing and be still,Are the two trades of man; and which is worseI know not, but I know that both are ill.\n\n- A.E. Housman, More Poems\n|\nHe's an intelligent man, but it takes something more than intelligence to act intelligently.\n\n- Fyodor\n|\nShare your love, share you happiness, care for others; your wealth will be endless.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nSuch was the hidden power of nature, capable of producing extreme beauty and cruelty at the same time.\n\n- Kenneth Eade, Political Thriller: Unwanted, an American Assassin Story: an assassination, vigilante justice and terrorism thriller\n|\nWe live on an island surrounded by a sea of ignorance. As our island of knowledge grows, so does the shore of our ignorance.\n\n- John\n|\nIt is easy to conform, but it takes great courage to stand up for peace.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nBefore you worry about the beauty of your body, worry about the health of your body.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nThe atoms of our body, as well, flow in and away from us. We, like waves and like all objects, are a flux of events; we are processes, for a brief time monotonous\n\n- Carlo Rovelli, La realtà non è come ci appare: La struttura elementare delle cose\n|\nIt is like reading two books, one with each eye, and understanding them both.\n\n- Dexter Palmer, The Dream of Perpetual Motion\n|\nI like the night. Without the dark, we'd never see the stars.\n\n- Stephenie Meyer, Twilight\n|\nThere was nothing particularly special about her, except that she was good with numbers, and very good at lying, and she made her home in between the pages of books.\n\n- Maggie Stiefvater, Linger\n|\nThe nonessential empl